      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake, 50 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Grease and line a 900 g loaf tin. Combine the {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{fine-sea-salt}}, and {{mustard-powder}} in a large bowl. Stir in 80 g of the grated {{mature-cheddar}}. Pour in the {{pale-ale}} and melted {{unsalted-butter}} and fold together with a spatula until just combined, a few streaks of flour are fine. This is a ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "quick bread",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp876o8v0000lgv49uwybr41"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": overmixing develops gluten and makes the crumb tight.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Scrape the batter into the prepared tin and scatter the remaining {{mature-cheddar}} over the top. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean and the crust is deep golden. An internal probe should read 90°C or above. Cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
